{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἁπᾰλός</b>, ή, όν, <br /> <b>soft to the touch, tender</b>: in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] mostly of the human body, ἁπαλὴν ὑπὸ δειρήν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 3.371; παρειάων ἁπαλάων 18.123; ἁπαλοῖο δι᾽ αὐχένος ἦλθεν ἀκωκή 17.49; ἁ. πόδες 19.92\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἁ. τέ σφ᾽ ἦτορ ἀπηύρα, i. e. the life of <b>young</b> animals,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 11.115; ἵεσαν αὐδὴν ἐξ ἁπαλῶν στομάτων 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 279; δέρα 7th-6th c.BC: Sappho Lyrica “Papyrus fragments” in E. Diehl, 23.16 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of persons, <b>delicate,</b> παῖδες[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus “Supp.” 14.5; εὐμορφοτέρα.. τᾶς ἀπάλας Γυρίννως 7th-6th c.BC: Sappho Lyrica 76 \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; of flowers, ἄνθρυσκα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Ead. “Supp.” 25.13\">Refs</a>]; rare in Trag., and only in Lyric poetry, παρειά[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 70; βρέφος ἁ. 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 1285; βλέφαρον τέγγουσ᾽ ἁ. “El.” 1339; more frequently in Comedy texts, σισύμβριον 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 239; κρέα 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 1063; δάκτυλοι 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 48; θερμολουσίαις ἁπαλοί “Comica Adespota” 56\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; so in Prose, ἁ. ψυχή[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 245a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of <b>raw</b> fruit, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.92, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 19.18 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of <b>tender</b> meat, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “An.” 1.5.2\">Refs</a>]; <b>soft-boiled,</b> of eggs, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" {5th c.AD}: Caelius Aurelianus Medicus “Anthologia Graeca” 2.18 \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]; of a <b>gentle</b> fire, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 79.8, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 3.25. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>soft, gentle,</b> ἁπαλὸν γελάσαι laugh <b>gently,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.465\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἁ. δίαιτα <b>soft,</b> <b>delicate,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 239c; τῶ αὐτῷ.. χρησώμεθα τεκμηρίῳ περὶ Ἔρωτα ὅτι ἁπαλός [prev. author] “Smp.” 195e (also in _superlative_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἁ. εἴσπλους λιμένος, opposed to τραχύς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 357. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>adverb</i> ἁπαλῶς, ὀπτᾶν to roast <b>moderately,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Sotades Lyricus Comedy texts 1.16\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> ἁπαλωτέρως, ἅπτεσθαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 37. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> in bad sense, <b>soft, weak,</b> ὡς ἁ. καὶ λευκὸς [οἶνος] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 183; λευκός, ἐξυρημένος, γυναικόφωνος, ἁ. 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 192\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. [ᾰπᾰλο; for καλάμῳ.. ὑπᾱπάλῳ, in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 28.4, is corrupt.]\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0527","accentedUnicode":"ἁπαλός","shortDef":"tender (referring to sprouts)","mediumDef":"tender (referring to sprouts) <br /><b>soft, tender,</b> <ref='Mat.24.32'>Mt. 24:32</ref>; <ref='Mrk.13.28'>Mk. 13:28</ref>*","stepGloss":"tender","stepTransliteration":"hapalos","count":2,"_es_Definition":"brotar las hojas, echar hojas, ponerse tierno","_zh_tw_Definition":"柔軟的","_zh_Definition":"柔软的","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"non; mềm non; cây đâm chồi","_zh_tw_Gloss":"嫩","_es_Gloss":"tierno","_zh_Gloss":"嫩"}]}